      {
        "title": "Acrobat",
        "excerpt": "Name     Tier     Type     Description                                      Crane Stance                  Novice         1-Action                                                        Fantastic Leap                  Novice         2-Action                                                        Flurry of Blows                  Novice         1-Action                                                        Incredible Movement                  Novice         Passive                                                        Reactive Pursuit                  Novice         Reaction                                                        Stunning Fist                  Novice         Free                                                        Agile Grace                  Veteran         Passive                                                        Sleeper Hold                  Veteran         1-Action                                                        Wall Run                  Veteran         1-Action                                                        Water Step                  Veteran         Passive                                                        Winding Flow                  Veteran         1-Action                                                        Whirlwind Strike                  Master         3-Action                                                        Enduring Quickness                  Epic         Passive                                                        Swift River                  Epic         Free                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 Crane Stance                              Novice                                       Stance                                                      Requirements           You are unarmored                                  You enter the stance of a crane, using flowing defensive motions. You gain a +1 bonus to AC, but the only Strikes you can make are crane wing attacks. These deal 1d6 bludgeoning damage, and have the agile, finesse, and unarmed traits.   While in Crane Stance, you gain a +5 bonus to skill rolls made to jump.                                  Fantastic Leap                              Novice                        You launch yourself through the air at a foe. Make a Leap or attempt a High Jump or Long Jump. At the end of your jump, you can make a melee Strike, even if you’re in mid-air. You fall to the ground after the Strike. If the distance of your fall is no more than the height of your jump, you take no damage and land upright.                                  Flurry of Blows                              Novice                                       Flourish                                 Make two melee Strikes. If both hit the same creature, combine their damage for the purpose of resistances and weaknesses. Apply your MAP to the Strikes normally.                                  Incredible Movement              Novice                        You move like the wind. Whenever you’re not wearing armor, you gain a bonus to your Speed equal to 5 feet * your Acrobat level.                                  Reactive Pursuit                              Novice                                             Trigger           An adjacent foe moves away from you, and you can reach at least one space adjacent to the foe with a Stride action                                  You keep pace with a retreating foe. You Stride, but you must end your movement adjacent to the triggering enemy. Your move does not trigger reactions from the triggering enemy.                                  Stunning Fist                              Novice                                       Incapacitation                                                      Prerequisites           Flurry of Blows                    Trigger           You target the same creature with two Strikes from your Flurry of Blows, and at least one of the Strikes hits and deals damage.                                  The focused power of your flurry threatens to overwhelm your opponent. Your target must succeed at a Fortitude save against a DC of 10 + Strength + Prof of be stunned 1 (or stunned 3 on a critical failure).                                  Agile Grace              Veteran                        Your graceful moves with agile weapons are beyond compare. Your multiple attack penalty with agile weapons becomes -3 for each attack action you’ve used so far this turn (rather than -4).                                  Sleeper Hold                              Veteran                                       Attack                    Incapacitation                                                      Requirements           You have a creature grabbed or restrained                                  You pinch crucial points of your target’s nervous system, impeding its ability to function. Attempt a Wrestling check to Grapple the creature, with the following success and critical success effects instead of the usual effects.                                   Critical Success           The target falls unconscious for 1 minute, though it remains standing and doesn't drop what it holds                             Success           The target takes a -1 penalty to Agility until the end of its next turn                                                                 Wall Run                              Veteran                        You defy gravity, traversing vertical planes as easily as the ground. Stride up to your Speed. You must start your movement on a horizontal surface. During this movement, you can run up vertical surfaces, like walls, at your full Speed. If you end the Stride off the ground, you fall after taking your next action or when your turn ends, whichever comes first. If you have Water Step or a similar ability, Wall Run lets you run along flimsy vertical surfaces, as well as vertical liquids, such as a waterfall.                                  Water Step              Veteran                        You can Stride across liquid and surfaces that don’t support your weight. This benefit only lasts during your movement. If you end your movement on a surface that can’t support you, you fall in or it collapses as normal.                                  Winding Flow                              Veteran                                             Frequency           Once per round                                  Any journey consists of more than simply reaching your destination. You use two of the following actions in any order: Stand, Step, and Stride. You can’t use the same action twice.                                  Whirlwind Strike                              Master                                       Flourish                    Open                                 You attack all nearby adversaries. Make a melee Strike against each enemy within your melee reach. Each attack counts towards your MAP, but do not increase your penalty until you have made all your attacks.                                  Enduring Quickness              Epic                        You move as fast and as high as the wind itself. You’re permanently quickened. You can use your extra action only to Stride or Leap.                                  Swift River                              Epic                                             Trigger           Your turn ends and you have a penalty to your Speed or are immobilized or slowed                                  You flow like water, avoiding all restraints. End one penalty to your speed, or end one immobilized or slowed condition affecting you.",
        "url": "/acrobat.html"
      }
      
