      {
        "title": "Hunter",
        "excerpt": "Name     Tier     Type     Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Far Shot                  Novice         Passive                                                        Hunt Prey                  Novice         1-Action                                                        Hunter's Aim                  Novice         2-Action                                                        Camouflage                  Veteran         Passive                                                        Deadly Aim                  Veteran         1-Action                                                        Debilitating Shot                  Veteran         2-Action                                                        Incredible Ricochet                  Veteran         2-Action                                                        Double Prey                  Master         Passive                                                        Legendary Shot                  Epic         Passive                                                        Shadow Hunter                  Epic         Passive                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Far Shot              Novice                        Your experience in the field has taught you how to focus your aim at a distance, increasing your accuracy. Double your weapons’ range increments.                                  Hunt Prey                              Novice                                       Concentrate                                                      Duration           24 hours, or until you use this power again                                  You designate a single creature as your prey and focus your attacks against that creature. You must be able to see or hear the prey, or you must be tracking the prey during exploration. You gain a +2 bonus to Perception rolls or Survival rolls made to Seek or Track your prey. You also ignore the penalty for making ranged attacks within your second increment against the prey you’re hunting. The first time you hit your hunted prey in a round, you also deal 1d8 additional precision damage.                                  Hunter's Aim                              Novice                                       Concentrate                                 By spending a moment to focus, you can ensure your attack strikes true. Make a ranged weapon Strike. On this Strike, you gain a +2 bonus to the attack roll and ignore the target’s concealed condition.                                  Camouflage              Veteran                        You alter your appearance to blend in to your surroundings. While outdoors, you can Sneak even if you’re observed.                                  Deadly Aim                              Veteran                                       Open                                 You aim for your prey’s weak spots, making your shot more challenging but dealing more damage if you hit. Make a ranged Strike against your hunted prey at a -2 penalty. Your Strike’s damage increases by 2 + Prof.                                  Debilitating Shot                              Veteran                                       Flourish                                 Aiming for a weak point, you impede your foe with a precise shot. Make a ranged weapon Strike. If it hits and deals damage, the target is slowed 1 until the end of its next turn.                                  Incredible Ricochet                              Veteran                                       Concentrate                    Press                                 After your first shot singles out your opponent’s position, you direct another that ricochets around obstacles and strikes unerringly. Make a ranged weapon Strike. You ignore the target’s concealed condition and all cover.                                  Double Prey              Master                                             Prerequisites           Hunt Prey                                  You can focus on two foes at once, hunting both of them down. When you use the Hunt Prey power, you can pick two creatures as your prey.                                  Legendary Shot              Epic                                             Prerequisites           Far Shot, Hunt Prey                                  Your focus on your hunted prey, perceiving angles, air resistance, and every variable that would affect your ranged attack. You can ignore the penalty for attacking up to five range increments away when attacking your hunted prey.                                  Shadow Hunter              Epic                                             Prerequisites           Camouflage                                  You blend in to your surroundings so well that others have trouble telling you apart from the terrain. While outdoors, you’re always concealed from all foes if you choose to be.",
        "url": "/hunter.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Juggernaut",
        "excerpt": "Name     Tier     Type     Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Double Shot                  Novice         2-Action                                                        Point-Blank Shot                  Novice         1-Action                                                        Supressive Fire                  Veteran         Passive                                                        Triple Shot                  Veteran         Passive                                                        Greater Supressive Fire                  Master         Passive                                                        Multishot Stance                  Master         1-Action                                                        Impossible Volley                  Epic         3-Action                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Double Shot                              Novice                                       Flourish                                                      Requirements           You are wielding a ranged weapon without the reload trait                                  You shoot twice in blindingly fast succession. Make two Strikes, each against a separate target and with a -2 penalty. Both attacks count towards MAP, but the penalty doesn’t increase until after you’ve made both of them.                                  Point-Blank Shot                              Novice                                       Open                    Stance                                                      Requirements           You are wielding a ranged weapon                                  You take aim to pick off nearby enemies quickly. When using a ranged weapon, you gain a +2 bonus to attacks against targets within 30 feet.                                  Supressive Fire              Veteran                        The overwhelming number of your attacks leaves an enemy flustered. If you critically hit a creature with a ranged weapon, or hit it at least twice on the same turn with a ranged weapon, it’s flat-footed until the start of your next turn.                                  Triple Shot              Veteran                                             Prerequisites           Double Shot                                  You can quickly fire multiple shots with greater control. When you use Double Shot, you can make the attacks against the same target. You can add an additional action to Double Shot to make three ranged Strikes instead of two. If you do, the penalty is -4 instead of -2. All attacks count toward MAP, but the penalty doesn’t increase until after you’ve made all of them.                                  Greater Supressive Fire              Master                                             Prerequisites           Supressive Fire                                  Even a single missile can throw off your enemy’s balance, and more powerful attacks leave it flustered for longer. If you hit a creature with a ranged weapon, it’s flat-footed until the start of your next turn. If you critically hit a creature or hit it twice on the same turn with a ranged weapon, it’s flat-footed until the end of your next turn instead.                                  Multishot Stance                              Master                                       Stance                                                      Prerequisites           Triple Shot                    Requirements           You are wielding a ranged weapon without the reload trait                                  You lock yourself in a stable position so you can fire swiftly and accurately. While you are in this stance, your penalty for Double Shot is reduced to -1, or -2 if you add the extra action to make three Strikes. If you move from your position, this stance ends.                                  Impossible Volley                              Epic                                       Flourish                    Open                                                      Requirements           You are wielding a ranged weapon without the reload trait                                  You fire a volley at all foes in an area. Make one Strike with a -2 penalty against each enemy within a 10-foot-radius burst. Roll the damage only once for all targets. Each attack counts towards MAP, but do not increase your penalty until you have made all your attacks.",
        "url": "/juggernaut.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Rogue",
        "excerpt": "Name     Tier     Type     Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Nimble Dodge                  Novice         Reaction                                                        Quick Draw                  Novice         1-Action                                                        Sneak Attack                  Novice         Passive                                                        Unbalancing Blow                  Novice         Passive                                                        Nimble Roll                  Veteran         Passive                                                        Sly Striker                  Veteran         Passive                                                        Defensive Roll                  Master         Free                                                        Impossible Striker                  Epic         Passive                                                        Master Strike                  Epic         Free                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Nimble Dodge                              Novice                                             Trigger           A creature targets you with an attack and you can see the attacker                                  You deftly dodge out of the way, gaining a +2 bonus to AC against the triggering attack.                                  Quick Draw                              Novice                        You draw your weapon and attack with the same motion. You Interact to draw a weapon, then Strike with that weapon.                                  Sneak Attack              Novice                        When your enemy can’t properly defend itself, you take advantage to deal extra damage. If you Strike a creature that has the flat-footed condition, you deal an extra 1d6 precision damage. The weapon you Strike with must be a ranged weapon, or must have the agile or finesse trait.   As your level increases, so does the number of damage dice for your sneak attack. Increase the number of dice to 2d6 at 5th level, 3d6 at 11th level, and 4d6 at 17th level.                                  Unbalancing Blow              Novice                        Interweaving your most powerful attacks in a graceful flow, you temporarily unbalance your foes. Whenever your Strike is a critical hit and deals damage, the target is flat-footed against your attacks until the end of your next turn.                                  Nimble Roll              Veteran                                             Prerequisites           Nimble Dodge                                  You throw yourself into a roll to escape imminent danger. You can use Nimble Dodge before attempting a Reflex save in addition to its original trigger. If you do, the circumstance bonus applies to your Reflex save against the triggering effect.   When you use Nimble Dodge and the triggering attack fails or criticalls fails, or when you succeed or critically succeed at the saving throw, you can also Stride up to 10 feet as part of the reaction. If you do, the reaction gains Move.                                  Sly Striker              Veteran                                             Prerequisites           Sneak Attack                                  Your attacks deal more damage, even against creatures that aren’t flat-footed. When you succeed or critically succeed at a Strike against a creature that isn’t flat-footed, you also deal 1d6 precision damage. This applies only if you’re using a weapon you could Sneak Attack with. This damage increases to 2d6 at 14th level.                                  Defensive Roll                              Master                                       Encounter                                                      Trigger           A physical attack would reduce you to 0 HP                                  Dropping into a roll to disperse the force of the blow, you can partially evade a lethal attack and stay conscious. You take half damage from the triggering attack.                                  Impossible Striker              Epic                                             Prerequisites           Sly Striker                                  Your attacks are swift and deadly beyond explanation. Nothing can prevent you from making a sneak attack, even if your opponent can see every blow coming. Instead of dealing the damage from Sly Striker, you can deal your full Sneak Attack damage to a target even if the target isn’t flat-footed.                                  Master Strike                              Epic                                       Incapacitation                                                      Trigger           Your Strike hits a flat-footed creature and deals damage                                  The target attempts a Fortitude save against a DC of 10 + Precision + Prof. It then becomes temporarily immune to your Master Strike for 1 day.                                   Critical Success           The target is unaffected                             Success           The target takes a -2 penalty to Strength until the end of your next turn                             Failure           The target is paralyzed for 4 rounds                             Critical Failure           The target is paralyzed for 4 rounds, knocked unconscious for 2 hours, or killed (your choice)",
        "url": "/rogue.html"
      }
      
