      {
        "title": "Fundamentalist",
        "excerpt": "Name     Tier     Type     Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Counterspell                  Novice         Reaction                                                        Dispel Magic                  Novice         2-Action                                                        Illusory Disguise                  Novice         2-Action                                                        Metamagic                  Novice         1-Action                                                        Misty Step                  Novice         1-Action                                                        Dimension Door                  Veteran         2-Action                                                        Greater Metamagic                  Veteran         Passive                                                        Resilient Sphere                  Veteran         2-Action                                                        Project Image                  Master         2-Action                                                        Redirect Gravity                  Master         3-Action                                                        Reflect Spell                  Master         Passive                                                        Metamagic Mastery                  Epic         Passive                                                        Time Stop                  Epic         3-Action                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Counterspell                              Novice                                             Trigger           A creature you can see within 60 feet casts a spell                    Cost           The amount of Mana the other caster expends                                  The other spell has no effect.                                  Dispel Magic                              Novice                                       Spell                                                      Cost           2 Mana                    Range           120 feet                    Target           One spell effect                                  You unravel the magic behind a spell or effect. Make a Sorcery roll against the Sorcery DC of the creature that cast the spell. If you succeed, the target spell immediately ends.                                  Illusory Disguise                              Novice                                       Spell                    Visual                                                      Cost           1 Mana                                  You create an illusion that causes you to appear as another creature of the same body shape, and with roughly similar height and weight as yourself. The disguise is typically good enough to hide your identity, but not to impersonate a specific individual. The spell doesn’t change your voice, scent, or mannerisms. You can change the appearance of your clothing and worn items, but held items are unaffected, and any worn item you remove returns to its true appearance.      Heightened (total 2 Mana)   The spell also disguises your voice and scent, and it gains the auditory trait   Heightened (total 3 Mana)   You can appear as any creature of the same size, even a specific individual as long as you’ve seen them before                                  Metamagic                              Novice                                       Concentrate                    Manipulate                                 You manipulate the energy of your spell, enhancing its effect. If the next action you use it to cast a spell, you modify the spell in one of the following ways.      Reach   Increase the spell’s range by 30 feet   Silent   The spell doesn’t require verbal components   Widen   If the spell’s area is a burst, increase its radius by 5 feet, or if the spell’s area is a line or cone, increase its length by 10 feet                                  Misty Step                              Novice                                       Spell                    Teleportation                                                      Cost           2 Mana                    Range           30 feet                                  You disappear in a swirl of mist, reappearing in a different location. You and any items you’re wearing or holding teleport to a clear space within range you can see.                                  Dimension Door                              Veteran                                       Spell                    Teleportation                                                      Cost           4 Mana                    Range           120 feet                                  Opening a door that bypasses normal space, you instantly transport yourself and any items you’re wearing or holding from your current space to a clear space within range you can see. If you attempt to bring another creature with you, the power fails.      Heightened (total 5 Mana)   The range increases to 1 mile, and you don’t need to be able to see your destination, as long as you have been there in the past and know its relative location and distance from you                                  Greater Metamagic              Veteran                                             Prerequisites           Metamagic                                  You can modify your spells in a broad variety of ways. Your Metamagic power gains the following options.      Conservation   If you spend at least 1 Mana on the spell, one spell you cast next turn costs 1 Mana less   Overwhelming   The spell ignores any resistances to acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic damage   Quickened   The spell takes 2 fewer actions to cast, but the strain involved means you can’t use Metamagic again until you take a long rest                                  Resilient Sphere                              Veteran                                       Force                    Spell                                                      Cost           4 Mana                    Range           30 feet                    Duration           1 minute                                  You create an immobile sphere of force to either trap or protect the target, blocking anything that would pass through the sphere. The sphere has AC 5, Hardness 10, and 40 HP. It’s immune to critical hits and precision damage. If the target is unwilling, it can make a Reflex save, with the following effect.                                   Critical Success           The target disrupts the sphere's integrity, causing it to collapse entirely                             Success           The sphere functions normally but has only 10 HP instead of 40                             Failure           The sphere has its normal effect                                                        Project Image                              Master                                       Mental                    Spell                                                      Cost           7 Mana                    Range           30 feet                    Duration           Sustained up to 1 minute                                  You project an illusory image of yourself. You must stay within range of the image, and if at any point you can’t see the image, the spell ends. Whenever you cast a spell, you can cause the spell effect to originate from either yourself or the image. Because the image is an illusion, it isn’t a creature and can’t benefit from spells. The image has the same AC and saves as you. If it is hit by an attack or fails a save, the spell ends.      Heightened (total 9 Mana)   The maximum duration you can Sustan the spell increases to 10 minutes                                  Redirect Gravity                              Master                                       Spell                                                      Cost           7 Mana                    Range           120 feet                    Area           30-foot burst                    Duration           1 minute                                  You change the direction of gravity in the area. Creatures and objects that aren’t secured to the ground immediately fall towards the new direction you designate as down. Rules for falling and fall damage apply as normal. A creature partially inside the area is caught between normal and redirected gravity, and is pulled in both directions at once.                                  Reflect Spell              Master                                             Prerequisites           Counterspell                                  When you use Counterspell to counteract a spell that affects targeted creatures or an area, you can turn that spell’s effect back on its caster. When reflected, the spell affects only the original caster, even if it’s area spell or it would normally affect more than one creature. The original caster can attempt a save and use other defenses against the reflected spell as normal.                                  Metamagic Mastery              Epic                                             Prerequisites           Metamagic                                  Altering your spells doesn’t take any longer than casting them normally. You can use Metamagic as a Free power.                                  Time Stop                              Epic                                       Spell                                                      Cost           10 Mana                                  You temporarily stop time for everything but yourself, allowing you to use several actions in what appears to others to be no time at all. Immediately after using this power, you take 3 turns. Rounds only pass for you, effects specifically targeting or affecting you, and effects you create during the stoppage. All other creatures and objects are invulnerable and can’t be targeted or affected by anything. Once you have finished your turns, time begins to flow again for the rest of the world.",
        "url": "/fundamentalist.html"
      }
      
