      {
        "title": "Greater Metamagic",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Prerequisites     Metamagic        You can modify your spells in a broad variety of ways. Your Metamagic power gains the following options.      Conservation   If you spend at least 1 Mana on the spell, one spell you cast next turn costs 1 Mana less   Overwhelming   The spell ignores any resistances to acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic damage   Quickened   The spell takes 2 fewer actions to cast, but the strain involved means you can’t use Metamagic again until you take a long rest",
        "url": "/greater-metamagic.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Resilient Sphere",
        "excerpt": "Force            Spell              Type   2-Action         Cost     4 Mana        Range     30 feet        Duration     1 minute        You create an immobile sphere of force to either trap or protect the target, blocking anything that would pass through the sphere. The sphere has AC 5, Hardness 10, and 40 HP. It’s immune to critical hits and precision damage. If the target is unwilling, it can make a Reflex save, with the following effect.                   Critical Success       The target disrupts the sphere's integrity, causing it to collapse entirely                 Success       The sphere functions normally but has only 10 HP instead of 40                 Failure       The sphere has its normal effect",
        "url": "/resilient-sphere.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Project Image",
        "excerpt": "Mental            Spell              Type   2-Action         Cost     7 Mana        Range     30 feet        Duration     Sustained up to 1 minute        You project an illusory image of yourself. You must stay within range of the image, and if at any point you can’t see the image, the spell ends. Whenever you cast a spell, you can cause the spell effect to originate from either yourself or the image. Because the image is an illusion, it isn’t a creature and can’t benefit from spells. The image has the same AC and saves as you. If it is hit by an attack or fails a save, the spell ends.      Heightened (total 9 Mana)   The maximum duration you can Sustan the spell increases to 10 minutes",
        "url": "/project-image.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Redirect Gravity",
        "excerpt": "Spell              Type   3-Action         Cost     7 Mana        Range     120 feet        Area     30-foot burst        Duration     1 minute        You change the direction of gravity in the area. Creatures and objects that aren’t secured to the ground immediately fall towards the new direction you designate as down. Rules for falling and fall damage apply as normal. A creature partially inside the area is caught between normal and redirected gravity, and is pulled in both directions at once.",
        "url": "/redirect-gravity.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Reflect Spell",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Prerequisites     Counterspell        When you use Counterspell to counteract a spell that affects targeted creatures or an area, you can turn that spell’s effect back on its caster. When reflected, the spell affects only the original caster, even if it’s area spell or it would normally affect more than one creature. The original caster can attempt a save and use other defenses against the reflected spell as normal.",
        "url": "/reflect-spell.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Metamagic Mastery",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Prerequisites     Metamagic        Altering your spells doesn’t take any longer than casting them normally. You can use Metamagic as a Free power.",
        "url": "/metamagic-mastery.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Time Stop",
        "excerpt": "Spell              Type   3-Action         Cost     10 Mana        You temporarily stop time for everything but yourself, allowing you to use several actions in what appears to others to be no time at all. Immediately after using this power, you take 3 turns. Rounds only pass for you, effects specifically targeting or affecting you, and effects you create during the stoppage. All other creatures and objects are invulnerable and can’t be targeted or affected by anything. Once you have finished your turns, time begins to flow again for the rest of the world.",
        "url": "/time-stop.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Far Shot",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Your experience in the field has taught you how to focus your aim at a distance, increasing your accuracy. Double your weapons’ range increments.",
        "url": "/far-shot.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Hunt Prey",
        "excerpt": "Concentrate              Type   1-Action         Duration     24 hours, or until you use this power again        You designate a single creature as your prey and focus your attacks against that creature. You must be able to see or hear the prey, or you must be tracking the prey during exploration. You gain a +2 bonus to Perception rolls or Survival rolls made to Seek or Track your prey. You also ignore the penalty for making ranged attacks within your second increment against the prey you’re hunting. The first time you hit your hunted prey in a round, you also deal 1d8 additional precision damage.",
        "url": "/hunt-prey.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Hunter's Aim",
        "excerpt": "Concentrate              Type   2-Action         By spending a moment to focus, you can ensure your attack strikes true. Make a ranged weapon Strike. On this Strike, you gain a +2 bonus to the attack roll and ignore the target’s concealed condition.",
        "url": "/hunter-s-aim.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Camouflage",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         You alter your appearance to blend in to your surroundings. While outdoors, you can Sneak even if you’re observed.",
        "url": "/camouflage.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Deadly Aim",
        "excerpt": "Open              Type   1-Action         You aim for your prey’s weak spots, making your shot more challenging but dealing more damage if you hit. Make a ranged Strike against your hunted prey at a -2 penalty. Your Strike’s damage increases by 2 + Prof.",
        "url": "/deadly-aim.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Debilitating Shot",
        "excerpt": "Flourish              Type   2-Action         Aiming for a weak point, you impede your foe with a precise shot. Make a ranged weapon Strike. If it hits and deals damage, the target is slowed 1 until the end of its next turn.",
        "url": "/debilitating-shot.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Incredible Ricochet",
        "excerpt": "Concentrate            Press              Type   2-Action         After your first shot singles out your opponent’s position, you direct another that ricochets around obstacles and strikes unerringly. Make a ranged weapon Strike. You ignore the target’s concealed condition and all cover.",
        "url": "/incredible-ricochet.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Double Prey",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Prerequisites     Hunt Prey        You can focus on two foes at once, hunting both of them down. When you use the Hunt Prey power, you can pick two creatures as your prey.",
        "url": "/double-prey.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Legendary Shot",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Prerequisites     Far Shot, Hunt Prey        Your focus on your hunted prey, perceiving angles, air resistance, and every variable that would affect your ranged attack. You can ignore the penalty for attacking up to five range increments away when attacking your hunted prey.",
        "url": "/legendary-shot.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Shadow Hunter",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Prerequisites     Camouflage        You blend in to your surroundings so well that others have trouble telling you apart from the terrain. While outdoors, you’re always concealed from all foes if you choose to be.",
        "url": "/shadow-hunter.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Double Shot",
        "excerpt": "Flourish              Type   2-Action         Requirements     You are wielding a ranged weapon without the reload trait        You shoot twice in blindingly fast succession. Make two Strikes, each against a separate target and with a -2 penalty. Both attacks count towards MAP, but the penalty doesn’t increase until after you’ve made both of them.",
        "url": "/double-shot.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Point-Blank Shot",
        "excerpt": "Open            Stance              Type   1-Action         Requirements     You are wielding a ranged weapon        You take aim to pick off nearby enemies quickly. When using a ranged weapon, you gain a +2 bonus to attacks against targets within 30 feet.",
        "url": "/point-blank-shot.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Supressive Fire",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         The overwhelming number of your attacks leaves an enemy flustered. If you critically hit a creature with a ranged weapon, or hit it at least twice on the same turn with a ranged weapon, it’s flat-footed until the start of your next turn.",
        "url": "/supressive-fire.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Triple Shot",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Prerequisites     Double Shot        You can quickly fire multiple shots with greater control. When you use Double Shot, you can make the attacks against the same target. You can add an additional action to Double Shot to make three ranged Strikes instead of two. If you do, the penalty is -4 instead of -2. All attacks count toward MAP, but the penalty doesn’t increase until after you’ve made all of them.",
        "url": "/triple-shot.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Greater Supressive Fire",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Prerequisites     Supressive Fire        Even a single missile can throw off your enemy’s balance, and more powerful attacks leave it flustered for longer. If you hit a creature with a ranged weapon, it’s flat-footed until the start of your next turn. If you critically hit a creature or hit it twice on the same turn with a ranged weapon, it’s flat-footed until the end of your next turn instead.",
        "url": "/greater-supressive-fire.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Multishot Stance",
        "excerpt": "Stance              Type   1-Action         Prerequisites     Triple Shot        Requirements     You are wielding a ranged weapon without the reload trait        You lock yourself in a stable position so you can fire swiftly and accurately. While you are in this stance, your penalty for Double Shot is reduced to -1, or -2 if you add the extra action to make three Strikes. If you move from your position, this stance ends.",
        "url": "/multishot-stance.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Impossible Volley",
        "excerpt": "Flourish            Open              Type   3-Action         Requirements     You are wielding a ranged weapon without the reload trait        You fire a volley at all foes in an area. Make one Strike with a -2 penalty against each enemy within a 10-foot-radius burst. Roll the damage only once for all targets. Each attack counts towards MAP, but do not increase your penalty until you have made all your attacks.",
        "url": "/impossible-volley.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Charming Words",
        "excerpt": "Auditory            Incapacitation            Linguistic            Mental            Spell              Type   1-Action         Cost     1 Mana        Range     30 feet        Save     Will        Duration     Until the start of your next turn        You whisper enchanting words to deflect your foe’s ire. The target must attempt a Will save.                   Critical Success       The target is unaffected                 Success       The target takes a -1 penalty to attack rolls and damage rolls against you                 Failure       The target can't use hostile actions against you                 Critical Failure       The target is stunned 1 and can't use hostile actions against you",
        "url": "/charming-words.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Command",
        "excerpt": "Auditory            Linguistic            Mental            Spell              Type   2-Action         Cost     1 Mana        Range     30 feet        Save     Will        Duration     Until the end of the target's next turn        You shout a command that’s hard to ignore. You can command the target to approach you, run away (as if it had the fleeing condition), release what it’s holding, drop prone, or stand in place. It can’t Delay or take any reactions until it has obeyed your command. The effects depend on the target’s Will save.      Heightened (total 5 Mana)   You can target up to 10 creatures                        Success       The creature is unaffected                 Failure       For the first action on its next turn, the creature must use a single action to do as you command                 Critical Failure       The target must use all its actions on its next turn to obey your command",
        "url": "/command.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Phantom Pain",
        "excerpt": "Mental            Spell              Type   2-Action         Cost     1 Mana        Range     30 feet        Save     Will        Duration     1 minute        Illusory pain wracks the target, dealing 2d4 mental damage and 1d4 persistent mental damage. The target must attempt a Will save.                   Critical Success       The target is unaffected                 Success       The target takes full initial damage but no persistent damage, and the spell ends immediately                 Failure       The target takes full initial and persistent damage, and the target is sickened 1                 Critical Failure       As failure, but the target is sickened 2",
        "url": "/phantom-pain.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Confusion",
        "excerpt": "Emotion            Mental            Spell              Type   2-Action         Cost     4 Mana        Range     30 feet        Save     Will        You befuddle your target with strange impulses, causing it to act randomly. The effects are determined by the target’s Will save. You can Dismiss the spell.      Heightened (total 8 Mana)   You can target up to 10 creatures                   Critical Success       The target is unaffected                 Success       The target babbles incoherently and is stunned 1                 Failure       The target is confused for 1 minute, and can attempt a new save at the end of each of its turns to end the confusion                 Critical Failure       The target is confused for 1 minute, with no save to end the effect early",
        "url": "/confusion.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Mind Reading",
        "excerpt": "Detection            Mental            Spell              Type   2-Action         Cost     3 Mana        Range     30 feet        Save     Will        Duration     1 round, or sustained up to 1 minute        With a cursory mental touch, you attempt to read the target’s mind. It must attempt a Will save. The target then becomes temporarily immune to your Mind Reading power for 1 hour.                   Critical Success       The target perceives vague surface thoughts from you                 Success       You find out whether the target's Intelligence is higher than, equal to, or lower than yours                 Failure       You perceive vague surface thoughts from the target, and you find out whether its Intelligence is higher than, equal to, or lower than yours                 Critical Failure       As failure, and for the duration of the spell, you can Sustain to detect the target's surface throughts again",
        "url": "/mind-reading.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Nimble Dodge",
        "excerpt": "Type   Reaction         Trigger     A creature targets you with an attack and you can see the attacker        You deftly dodge out of the way, gaining a +2 bonus to AC against the triggering attack.",
        "url": "/nimble-dodge.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Quick Draw",
        "excerpt": "Type   1-Action         You draw your weapon and attack with the same motion. You Interact to draw a weapon, then Strike with that weapon.",
        "url": "/quick-draw.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Sneak Attack",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         When your enemy can’t properly defend itself, you take advantage to deal extra damage. If you Strike a creature that has the flat-footed condition, you deal an extra 1d6 precision damage. The weapon you Strike with must be a ranged weapon, or must have the agile or finesse trait.   As your level increases, so does the number of damage dice for your sneak attack. Increase the number of dice to 2d6 at 5th level, 3d6 at 11th level, and 4d6 at 17th level.",
        "url": "/sneak-attack.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Unbalancing Blow",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Interweaving your most powerful attacks in a graceful flow, you temporarily unbalance your foes. Whenever your Strike is a critical hit and deals damage, the target is flat-footed against your attacks until the end of your next turn.",
        "url": "/unbalancing-blow.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Nimble Roll",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Prerequisites     Nimble Dodge        You throw yourself into a roll to escape imminent danger. You can use Nimble Dodge before attempting a Reflex save in addition to its original trigger. If you do, the circumstance bonus applies to your Reflex save against the triggering effect.   When you use Nimble Dodge and the triggering attack fails or criticalls fails, or when you succeed or critically succeed at the saving throw, you can also Stride up to 10 feet as part of the reaction. If you do, the reaction gains Move.",
        "url": "/nimble-roll.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Sly Striker",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Prerequisites     Sneak Attack        Your attacks deal more damage, even against creatures that aren’t flat-footed. When you succeed or critically succeed at a Strike against a creature that isn’t flat-footed, you also deal 1d6 precision damage. This applies only if you’re using a weapon you could Sneak Attack with. This damage increases to 2d6 at 14th level.",
        "url": "/sly-striker.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Defensive Roll",
        "excerpt": "Encounter              Type   Free         Trigger     A physical attack would reduce you to 0 HP        Dropping into a roll to disperse the force of the blow, you can partially evade a lethal attack and stay conscious. You take half damage from the triggering attack.",
        "url": "/defensive-roll.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Impossible Striker",
        "excerpt": "Type   Passive         Prerequisites     Sly Striker        Your attacks are swift and deadly beyond explanation. Nothing can prevent you from making a sneak attack, even if your opponent can see every blow coming. Instead of dealing the damage from Sly Striker, you can deal your full Sneak Attack damage to a target even if the target isn’t flat-footed.",
        "url": "/impossible-striker.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Master Strike",
        "excerpt": "Incapacitation              Type   Free         Trigger     Your Strike hits a flat-footed creature and deals damage        The target attempts a Fortitude save against a DC of 10 + Precision + Prof. It then becomes temporarily immune to your Master Strike for 1 day.                   Critical Success       The target is unaffected                 Success       The target takes a -2 penalty to Strength until the end of your next turn                 Failure       The target is paralyzed for 4 rounds                 Critical Failure       The target is paralyzed for 4 rounds, knocked unconscious for 2 hours, or killed (your choice)",
        "url": "/master-strike.html"
      }
      
